HEADWORD: Archæology
<hw>Ar`ch⟦ae⟧*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(⟦aum⟧r`k⟦esl⟧*⟦ocr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*j⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'archaiologi`a</grk>; <grk>'archai^os</grk>
ancient (fr. <grk>'archh`</grk> beginning) + <grk>lo`gos</grk>
discourse, <grk>le`gein</grk> to speak.]</ety> <def>The science or study
of antiquities, esp. prehistoric antiquities, such as the remains of
buildings or monuments of an early epoch, inscriptions, implements, and
other relics, written manuscripts, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

